.@OfficialFBOP has been blocking information on how to claim a missing stimulus payment from reaching people behind the wall.

@RepDannyDavis and I wrote a letter demanding answers.

https://t.co/MIxsIfVkg8

Massachusetts’ eviction moratorium expires tomorrow and thousands of renters are at risk. 

@MassGovernor, do the right thing. Extend the eviction moratorium now. 

https://t.co/eIrEQinaph

For over 20 years, mifepristone has proven to be a safe, effective way to end an early pregnancy. It should not be so difficult to access.

@US_FDA must suspend the in-person distribution requirement for mifepristone immediately.
https://t.co/k5KaL6bNlr

Systemic racism is a public health crisis, and the first step towards ending it is to invest in policies and research that are actively anti-racist. 

@SenWarren, @RepBarbaraLee, and I have a bill to do exactly that.

https://t.co/lT4T1IfwgM

Yes, and the grace period for the federal eviction moratorium in the CARES Act expired yesterday.

@SenateMajLdr must call the Senate back into session and bring the HEROES Act to the floor.
https://t.co/CRzkRs1Ewa

The education of Black girls is often disrupted by discriminatory, overly punitive discipline policies that push them out of school.

@TheJusticeDept &amp; @BetsyDevosEd: you must intervene. 

cc: @RepRashida, @RepDebDingell, @RepLawrence, @RepAndyLevin, @RepHaleyStevens https://t.co/brE1cGMrCv

For 43 years, the Hyde Amendment has restricted access to abortion care and perpetuated inequity &amp; injustice.

@RepBarbaraLee, @RepSchakowsky, @RepAOC and I just filed an amendment to repeal it once and for all. #BeBoldEndHyde
https://t.co/UNEHiZsBrR

The Northeast is struggling with the highest rates of COVID-19 and over 10% of the country's food insecurity, but somehow we're only receiving 4% of @USDA's food aid. 

This doesn't add up.

@RepMcGovern and I are demanding that these critical resources be distributed equitably. https://t.co/amAPmSAVw2

I am deeply troubled by these reports. 

@CDCgov wasn't collecting &amp; reporting racial &amp; ethnic data on #COVID19 patients either until my colleagues &amp; I demanded it. 

Racism is systemic &amp; deeply entrenched in many of the institutions meant to protect us. It must be rooted out. https://t.co/I9QkCmlz7R

Congressional intent is powerful. 

It’s long past time that Congress declare its intent to end the scourge of police brutality in America by condemning all acts of police brutality, racial profiling, and excessive force. We must act boldly to #SaveLivesNow.

@amjoyshow https://t.co/WhX5tWwJjM

Micro businesses are the backbones of our communities, but so far, too many have been left out &amp; left behind by our federal relief efforts. 

@SenKamalaHarris &amp; I are introducing the #SavingOurStreet Act to get these businesses the support they need.

https://t.co/X5w4maBIRg

We need data on who's receiving federal economic relief so we can ensure the hardest-hit communities are getting the resources they need.

That's why @SenKamalaHarris @RepGregoryMeeks &amp; I are calling on @stevenmnuchin1 to publicly release data on #PPP recipients.

@BasicBlackWGBH https://t.co/mgnsSeF7Li

We must be equitable in our relief efforts amidst this crisis. 

@USedgov’s decision to exclude our undocumented students from emergency assistance is cruel and serves no purpose other than to further marginalize vulnerable communities. Shameful. 
https://t.co/seF6bcIZmE

